The paper focuses on speech emotion recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing and speech processing. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new loss function and evaluates it on a dataset, which falls under the scope of machine learning and deep learning. Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The proposed method involves using Siamese networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, indicating a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves the classification of emotions, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category as well.
